# NET-NEW under lead-uiwu (CRITICAL clone-path regression). FACET 3 (CA trust before
# clone). EMPIRICAL FINDING (product authority, 2026-06-28, reproduced launching
# shopsystem-templates against bc-base/launcher v0.3.33): after the /workspace chown
# (facet 2), the clone — routed via the agent-vault HTTPS_PROXY MITM — fails "SSL
# certificate problem: unable to get local issuer certificate" because the container's
# git does not trust the agent-vault proxy MITM CA at clone time. Single behavior: the
# launched BC has installed the agent-vault MITM root CA into its trust store BEFORE the
# clone runs, so a clone routed through HTTPS_PROXY passes TLS verification.
#
# CONNECTS to the ADR-045 / lead-lu91 CA-inline contract: AGENT_VAULT_CA_PEM carries the
# broker root CA as INLINE PEM CONTENT (not a path), and the bc-base entrypoint
# materializes the trust file from that value. This scenario pins the launch/container
# OBSERVABLE downstream of that contract — TLS through the proxy actually verifies at
# clone time — distinct from the producer/transport delivery pinned by templates scenario
# 200 (@scenario_hash:7ce09202755b0503) and from the bc-base entrypoint materialization
# pinned bc-internally by lead-b14a (features/bc_base_agent_vault_entrypoint.feature,
# @bc_internal — not on the lead host).
#
# COEXISTENCE the architect must enumerate at dispatch:
#   - templates scenario 200 (@scenario_hash:7ce09202755b0503) — delivers the CA as
#     inline PEM CONTENT to the leaf trust file (producer/transport side). 68 is the
#     launcher-side consequence: with that CA trusted, the proxied clone's TLS verifies.
#     Complementary across BCs; no conflict.
#   - scenario 47 (@scenario_hash, launch gates on agent-vault reachability) and the
#     scenario 45/46 broker family — broker REACHABILITY / credential brokering;
#     orthogonal to CA TRUST at clone time. Coexists unchanged.
#   - depends on facet-1/facet-2 fixes (a clone must be attempted, into a writable
#     /workspace) before the TLS leg is reachable; sequencing the architect carries.
#
# Pin observable launch/container behavior only (ADR-018; no BC source read). @bc: and
# the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the block-only
# @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
  @scenario_hash:0d29c76818a323a1
  Scenario: a launched BC trusts the agent-vault MITM proxy CA before the clone runs so a clone routed through HTTPS_PROXY passes TLS verification
    Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
    And the agent-vault broker root CA is delivered to the launched BC as inline PEM content via "AGENT_VAULT_CA_PEM" per ADR-045
    And the launched BC routes outbound HTTPS through the agent-vault MITM proxy via "HTTPS_PROXY"
    When bc-container launch is run with BC name "shopsystem-templates" and the in-container clone of its remote is performed through "HTTPS_PROXY"
    Then the running container has installed the agent-vault MITM root CA into its git/system trust store before the clone is attempted
    And the clone routed through "HTTPS_PROXY" completes its TLS handshake without an "SSL certificate problem: unable to get local issuer certificate" error
